{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MzpQZJ9GkSdxWfNLUjqe47","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.barista.health;\n     2→\n     3→import org.eclipse.microprofile.health.HealthCheck;\n     4→import org.eclipse.microprofile.health.HealthCheckResponse;\n     5→import org.eclipse.microprofile.health.Readiness;\n     6→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     7→\n     8→@Readiness\n     9→@ApplicationScoped\n    10→public class BasicHealth implements HealthCheck {\n    11→    @Override\n    12→    public HealthCheckResponse call() {\n    13→        return HealthCheckResponse.up(\"barista-service\");\n    14→    }\n    15→}\n    16→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"69da0444-5130-4df0-8627-2b3179c5983f","uuid":"4178fa77-512b-446e-b4ed-42ec2d42103e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Wp78fXajjaUEdbUoEVjyLb","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.barista.messaging;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import jakarta.json.bind.Jsonb;\n     5→import jakarta.json.bind.JsonbBuilder;\n     6→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming;\n     7→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Outgoing;\n     8→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Message;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.HashMap;\n    11→import java.util.Map;\n    12→\n    13→@ApplicationScoped\n    14→public class BaristaConsumer {\n    15→\n    16→    private final Jsonb jsonb = JsonbBuilder.create();\n    17→\n    18→    // Consumes commands from orders-service (topic: barista-commands)\n    19→    @Incoming(\"barista\")\n    20→    // Publishes order status updates (topic: order-updates)\n    21→    @Outgoing(\"order-updates\")\n    22→    public Message<String> makeCoffee(String orderJson) {\n    23→        try {\n    24→            System.out.println(\"[barista] received: \" + orderJson);\n    25→            // Parse whatever orders-service sent (JSON String)\n    26→            Map<String, Object> in = jsonb.fromJson(orderJson, Map.class);\n    27→\n    28→            // Carry through orderId if present (original Quarkus did this)\n    29→            Object orderId = in.get(\"orderId\");\n    30→\n    31→            Map<String, Object> out = new HashMap<>();\n    32→            if (orderId != null) {\n    33→                out.put(\"orderId\", orderId);\n    34→            }\n    35→            out.put(\"status\", \"READY\");\n    36→            out.put(\"from\", \"barista\");\n    37→\n    38→            // Produce clean JSON (no backslashes)\n    39→            return Message.of(jsonb.toJson(out));\n    40→\n    41→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    42→            System.err.println(\"[barista] parse/update error: \" + e + \" payload=\" + orderJson);\n    43→            // Let the framework nack and surface the error rather than emitting malformed JSON\n    44→            throw e;\n    45→        }\n    46→    }\n    47→}\n    48→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"69da0444-5130-4df0-8627-2b3179c5983f","uuid":"e2ea3dbc-70ab-46ea-ac89-19efcc01c42a"}
