{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KZes9P3bGKUhWDAJtuq3CJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.orders.messaging;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n     4→import org.springframework.kafka.core.KafkaTemplate;\n     5→import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n     6→\n     7→@Component\n     8→public class OrdersPipeline {\n     9→\n    10→    private final KafkaTemplate<String, String> kafkaTemplate;\n    11→    private final ObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper();\n    12→\n    13→    public OrdersPipeline(KafkaTemplate<String, String> kafkaTemplate) {\n    14→        this.kafkaTemplate = kafkaTemplate;\n    15→    }\n    16→\n    17→    public void publishToBarista(OrderCommand cmd) {\n    18→        try {\n    19→            System.out.println(\"[orders] sending barista command: \" + cmd);\n    20→            kafkaTemplate.send(\"barista-commands\", objectMapper.writeValueAsString(cmd));\n    21→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    22→            System.err.println(\"[orders] failed to send barista command: \" + e);\n    23→        }\n    24→    }\n    25→\n    26→    public void publishToKitchen(OrderCommand cmd) {\n    27→        try {\n    28→            System.out.println(\"[orders] sending kitchen command: \" + cmd);\n    29→            kafkaTemplate.send(\"kitchen-commands\", objectMapper.writeValueAsString(cmd));\n    30→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    31→            System.err.println(\"[orders] failed to send kitchen command: \" + e);\n    32→        }\n    33→    }\n    34→\n    35→    // simple DTO for messages\n    36→    public record OrderCommand(String target, long orderId, String item, int quantity) {}\n    37→}\n    38→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"69da0444-5130-4df0-8627-2b3179c5983f","uuid":"cb6433ee-7ffd-4766-a9b7-77fe1fb78797"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01CxSGT5uMWREE4aYJTogwxj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The issue is the KafkaTemplate.send() will block trying to get metadata from a non-existent Kafka broker. Let me rewrite the OrdersPipeline to be completely optional about Kafka. I'll use `@Autowired(required = false)` and make it fully fire-and-forget:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":785,"cache_read_input_tokens":127807,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":785,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":679},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"69da0444-5130-4df0-8627-2b3179c5983f","uuid":"712bcb41-02a2-4816-9381-3c14c5e354aa"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01CxSGT5uMWREE4aYJTogwxj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01GjG9Jw1QbjbK1A2MABpEor","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/messaging/OrdersPipeline.java","content":"package com.coffeeshop.orders.messaging;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Value;\nimport org.springframework.kafka.core.KafkaTemplate;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n\n@Component\npublic class OrdersPipeline {\n\n    @Autowired(required = false)\n    private KafkaTemplate<String, String> kafkaTemplate;\n\n    @Value(\"${spring.kafka.enabled:false}\")\n    private boolean kafkaEnabled;\n\n    private final ObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper();\n\n    public void publishToBarista(OrderCommand cmd) {\n        if (!kafkaEnabled || kafkaTemplate == null) {\n            System.out.println(\"[orders] Kafka disabled, skipping barista command: \" + cmd);\n            return;\n        }\n        try {\n            System.out.println(\"[orders] sending barista command: \" + cmd);\n            kafkaTemplate.send(\"barista-commands\", objectMapper.writeValueAsString(cmd));\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            System.err.println(\"[orders] failed to send barista command: \" + e);\n        }\n    }\n\n    public void publishToKitchen(OrderCommand cmd) {\n        if (!kafkaEnabled || kafkaTemplate == null) {\n            System.out.println(\"[orders] Kafka disabled, skipping kitchen command: \" + cmd);\n            return;\n        }\n        try {\n            System.out.println(\"[orders] sending kitchen command: \" + cmd);\n            kafkaTemplate.send(\"kitchen-commands\", objectMapper.writeValueAsString(cmd));\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            System.err.println(\"[orders] failed to send kitchen command: \" + e);\n        }\n    }\n\n    // simple DTO for messages\n    public record OrderCommand(String target, long orderId, String item, int quantity) {}\n}\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":785,"cache_read_input_tokens":127807,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":785,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":679},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"69da0444-5130-4df0-8627-2b3179c5983f","uuid":"dbfb674a-f1a5-4b9c-91a6-510b163770df"}
